The four teenage girls from the BBC World Service programme All That Stands In The Way, meet for the very first time. Lulu from London, Shoeshoe from Lesotho, Vigdis from Iceland and Mira from Jordan discuss their reaction to seeing each otherâ€™s lives and experiences depicted on the BBC. What has made them question their choices and freedoms and how do they see gender equality as they stand on the threshold of adulthood? (Photo: From top-left clockwise, Shoeshoe from Lesotho, Vigdis from Iceland and Mira from Jordan and Lulu from London) Show less